South Africa is now on a level 4 lockdown and there is likely to be more traffic on the road. JOHANNESBURG - Minister of Transport Fikile Mbalula briefed the media on COVID-19 lockdown regulations and directives related to transport. South Africa is now on a level 4 lockdown and there is likely to be more traffic on the road. More activity means authorities need to be on high alert to ensure the lockdown guidelines are observed. The total number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa has risen to 5647 with a death toll at 103.